      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KAMARAN (4) continues to race well having only once missed a place in his last eights starts, winning four of them. Came from a 20m handicap and raced three wide without cover so did well to box on for third last start. Proven at this venue and is suited back to a mobile start and a front row draw. There was plenty to like about the latest performance of DISTANT SUN (8) when he came from a 40m handicap to place at Cranbourne. Will enjoy a pretty soft run from this draw and the sprint lane is in play. Contender. DESERT ASSASSIN (10) draws on the back row but delivered a last-start win by 5.7 metres at Cranbourne. With even luck he could go on with it. BUSLIN BRODY (3) draws well and could be close to a win after finishing runner-up in his last two outings.",
